You ſee My Friends, firſt, How a Man Lives; 

                  •
               is by his Breath. Secondly, How a Man Dies; Tis by his Breath going forth. Thirdly; What becomes of a Man, when he Dies. Firſt, The Man; He returns to his Earth. Secondly, The Thoughts of the Man; They Periſh in that very Day. Each of theſe Articles, is to be diſtinctly conſidered.

In the Year, 1704 I find this Memorial en

